1. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) - The paper deals with phase retrieval and super-resolution, which are important topics in computer vision. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses a novel approach based on geometric quantization scheme of phase-less linear measurements, which is related to information theory. 
3. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper deals with image processing and super-resolution, which are important topics in multimedia. 
4. cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) - The paper discusses a recovery scheme for phase retrieval, which involves numerical analysis techniques. 
5. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - Although less likely, this paper could also be related to social and information networks as it discusses a method for comparing pairs of coded diffraction patterns across frequencies.
